rComments: Hands down the best lecturer at the iSchool. Lectures are engaging and you can tell how passionate the prof is about the course topic/teaching in general. Super supportive of students with multiple office hours - his office hours are always booked though so book early!

He's an amazing instructor and he's obviously passionate about the content. He doesn't really reply to emails but is really approachable in class and at OH, he listens to concerns and helps you get better and gives good feedback (when asked, since he doesn't really mark assignments).
my favourite professor at U of T
Great voice, approachable, clear, and funny. Only downside is that he's pretty hot so if you're into dudes, it could be distracting.
Awesome prof! Super funny, makes attending class a joy. I learned a lot in this course.

He is a great lecturer. He makes class fun, has discussions about recent developments in tech, personable, friendly, genuinely interested in teaching and his students. This class is one long group project, with no tests or exam. He is my favourite professor at U of T.
He's the Jesus of Computer Science undergrad. The second coming is real. All hail the king.
Great Guy. Really smart and really helpful, hope he goes far.
He was a great professor, made the class fun, and helped us understand difficult topics.
